ntain immune system health and support general health and wellbeing. It’s a delicious way to help support kids’ daily wellbeing, it contain ingredients such as zinc and vitamins C, D & E that assist healthy growth and development. Good health changes everything—support your child’s immune system with BLACKMORES Superkids Immune Chewables. Product Format Chewable Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Kids Health Immune System Health General Health No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Contains 4 essential nutrients to help support kids&#x27; immune system function: Zinc is a factor in the maintenance of general wellbeing and helps to support normal immune function. Vitamin C ascorbic acid which is known for its role normal functioning of the immune system. Vitamin C is widely found in fruits and vegetables. Good sources include blackcurrants, guava, citrus and kiwi fruit and vegetables such as broccoli, capsicum and sprouts. However, research undertaken in 2014-15 found that only one in twenty (5.1%) of Australian children were meeting the minimum number of serves of fruit and vegetables each day*. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system and is found in a limited range of foods. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system which can be found in a limited range of foods and produced from skin exposure to sunlight. Vitamin E is required for normal immune system function and Beta carotene (pro vitamin A) directly and indirectly supports immune function. *http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats Dosage Children 2-12 years Chew (do not swallow whole) 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Use only under adult supervision. Not recommended for children under 2 years. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN. Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. Excess consumption may have a laxative effect If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Contains 4 essential nutrients to help support kids&#x27; immune system function: Zinc is a factor in the maintenance of general wellbeing and helps to support normal immune function. Vitamin C ascorbic acid which is known for its role normal functioning of the immune system. Vitamin C is widely found in fruits and vegetables. Good sources include blackcurrants, guava, citrus and kiwi fruit and vegetables such as broccoli, capsicum and sprouts. However, research undertaken in 2014-15 found that only one in twenty (5.1%) of Australian children were meeting the minimum number of serves of fruit and vegetables each day*. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system and is found in a limited range of foods. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system which can be found in a limited range of foods and produced from skin exposure to sunlight. Vitamin E is required for normal immune system function and Beta carotene (pro vitamin A) directly and indirectly supports immune function. *http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats Children 2-12 years Chew (do not swallow whole) 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Use only under adult supervision. Not recommended for children under 2 years. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN. Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. Excess consumption may have a laxative effect If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Ingredients Active ingredients per chewable tablet: d-alpha-tocopheryl acid succinate 5.8 mg equivalent vitamin E 7 IU Zinc citrate dihydrate 9.3 mg equivalent dihydrate zinc 3 mg Calcium ascorbate dihydrate 99.4 mg equivalent ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 82.2 mg Betacarotene 450 micrograms Colecalciferol 5 micrograms equivalent vitamin D3 200 IU Superkids™ Immune Chewables Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Practices Terms Of Purchase Terms of Service Posting Guidelines Social Media House Rules Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Practices Terms Of Purchase Terms of Service Posting Guidelines Social Media House Rules Contacts & FAQs Report a Suspected Adverse Experience Contact Us Ask a Naturopath Product & Purchasing FAQs Blackmores Subscribe Contacts & FAQs Report a Suspected Adverse Experience Contact Us Ask a Naturopath Product & Purchasing FAQs Blackmores Subscribe Back To Top Terms of Purchase Privacy Pol