 C 500 Sustained Release Tablets All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Bio C® 500 Sustained Release Size Size 200 tablets Blackmores Bio C® 500 Sustained Release is specially formulated to deliver a gradual supply of vitamin C over 8 hours. It includes mineral ascorbates, a less acidic form of vitamin C that’s gentler on the stomach, plus bioflavonoids. This one-a-day formula helps reduce free radical damage to body cells, supports immune system health, and supports general health and wellbeing. It also supports collagen formation. Taken daily, it helps maintain vitamin C levels in the body throughout the day. Good health changes everything - support your vitamin C routine with Blackmores Bio C® 500 Sustained Release. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Immune System Health Common Colds & Flu Antioxidant for Free Radical Damage General Health No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Delivers a gradual supply of vitamin C over 8 hours. Buffered with mineral ascorbates making it gentle on the stomach. Added bioflavonoids thought to support the efficacy of vitamin C. Supports immune system health. Reduces the duration and severity of common cold symptoms. Antioxidant to decrease free radical damage to body cells. Supports wound healing and collagen formation. Maintains blood vessel health. Supports general health and wellbeing. Dosage Adults For immune system health : Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. To reduce the duration and severity of common cold symptoms : Take 1 tablet two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Adults only. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains phenylalanine and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Delivers a gradual supply of vitamin C over 8 hours. Buffered with mineral ascorbates making it gentle on the stomach. Added bioflavonoids thought to support the efficacy of vitamin C. Supports immune system health. Reduces the duration and severity of common cold symptoms. Antioxidant to decrease free radical damage to body cells. Supports wound healing and collagen formation. Maintains blood vessel health. Supports general health and wellbeing. Adults For immune system health : Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. To reduce the duration and severity of common cold symptoms : Take 1 tablet two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Adults only. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains phenylalanine and sulfites. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 280 mg Calcium ascorbate dihydrate 266 mg equivalent ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 220 mg Total vitamin C 500 mg Citrus bioflavonoids extract 25 mg Hesperidin 25 mg Rutoside 50 mg Rosa canina (rosehips) extract dry conc. 41.7 mg equivalent dry fruit 250 mg Bio C® 500 Sustained Release Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Bl